properties.name: Boba Shop
properties.description: Posted by Thejames It was quite a surprise to find an authentic boba shop all the way out here... The shop was actually very nice, very nice decor, and clean. I recall that they had some games there, like a deck of playing cards and a chinese checkers set... It was just so weird... it felt like "home"... like Southern California, but as I stared out the window, it was so very East Coast. Winter in the East Coast. Two heart stickers made their way onto companion electronics... an old Fujifilm FinePix, and a new Toshiba Dynabook. Across the street, there was some kind of bike store and costume shop. I watched her go into the stores, tired from all the studying and writing. I sat on a sofa-ish seat... she at the table. Two older guys sat about two tables away... they looked like they could be professors, and talked loudly for a long time about various issues, politics, and etc.

properties.name: CVS Pharmacy
properties.description: Posted by Thejames The cashier was able to tell I was wearing a Kenneth Cole watch with me wearing a fairly large coat, not exactly showing much of my right wrist...

properties.name: Campus Police?
properties.description: Posted by ThejamesIf I recall correctly, this was the place I went to ask for directions first, since I got lost after getting off the train. This was some kind of security place, or a small campus police station of sorts.

properties.name: College Park Station (East/Wrong Side)
properties.description: Posted by Thejames There\'s nothing on this side of the station... There is a UoM shuttle stop here, but I wasn\'t sure where in UoM it would drop us off at, and how I would get to the hotel from the dropoff point... so I opted not to try to take it. Across the street was an FDA building. Deciding to try and go south on River Road was a terrible decision that I would have to undo.

properties.name: College Park Station (West/correct Side)
properties.description: Posted by ThejamesI didn\'t get exit the station here the first time... boy did I have to walk a long way that day. And it got so windy up on Paint Branch Parkway... I almost couldn\'t move forward, had to lean forward a lot...
